file.name: am-title_manager.yml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.1
info:
  title: Title Manager
  description: 'This is a Library''s TItle Manager (INT) server.'
  contact:
    email: test@test.com
  version: 0.0.1
externalDocs:
  description: Find out more about Title Manager in Wiki
  url: https://library.test.com/docs/title
servers:
- url: https://stg-library.test.com/api/titles
tags:
- name: titles
  description: Access titles
  externalDocs:
    description: Find out more
    url: https://confluence.
- name: bulk
  description: Bulk Access
paths:
  /titles/{id}:
    put:
      tags:
      - titles
      summary: Update an existing title by ID
      operationId: updateTitle
      parameters:
        - name: id
          in: path
          description: Title's unique ID (Mongo ID).
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      requestBody:
        description: Title object that needs to be added to the db
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/Title'
        required: true
      responses:
        200:
          description: Successfully updated
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Title'
        400:
          description: Invalid body supplied
          content: {}
        404:
          description: Title not found
          content: {}
      security:
      - am_auth:
        - write:titles
        - read:titles
      x-codegen-request-body-name: body
    get:
      tags:
      - titles
      summary: Finds Titles by status
      description: Multiple status values can be provided with comma separated strings
      operationId: findTitlesById
      parameters:
        - name: id
          in: path
          description: Title's unique ID (Mongo ID).
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: Successfully updated
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Title'
        400:
          description: Invalid ID format supplied
          content: {}
        404:
          description: Title not found
          content: {}
      security:
      - am_auth:
        - read:titles
    delete:
      tags:
      - titles
      summary: Deletes a title
      operationId: deleteTitle
      parameters:
        - name: id
          in: path
          description: Title's unique ID (Mongo ID).
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        400:
          description: Invalid ID supplied
          content: {}
        404:
          description: Title not found
          content: {}
      security:
      - am_auth:
        - write:titles
        - read:titles
  /titles/bulk:
    get:
      tags:
      - bulk
      summary: Bulk Create Titles
      description: Create multiple titles in a single request.
      operationId: createBulkTitles
      responses:
        200:
          description: Successful operation
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: array
                items:
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/Title'
        400:
          description: Invalid title value
          content: {}
      deprecated: false
      security:
      - am_auth:
        - write:titles
        - read:titles  
components:
  schemas:
    Title:
      required:
      - source
      - name
      type: object
      properties:
        source:
          title: The source of the title
          type: string
        status:
          type: string
        name:
          type: string
        isbn:
          type: string
        created_at:
          type: string
        updated_at:
          type: string
        source_id:
          type: string
        id:
          type: string
  securitySchemes:
    am_auth:
      type: oauth2
      flows:
        implicit:
          authorizationUrl: https://stg-library.test.com/oauth
          scopes:
            write:titles: modify titles in your account
            read:titles: read your titles
    api_key:
      type: apiKey
      name: api_key
      in: header
